HEADWORD: Pavo
<hw>Pa"vo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
peacock. See <er>Peacock</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of birds, including the peacocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The Peacock, a constellation of
the southern hemisphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pavon</ent>⟦br⟧
